messages.msgSnippet: In a message dated 7/21/99 8:09:06 AM Eastern Daylight Time, mseger@mindspring.com writes:
messages.messageBody:
In a message dated 7/21/99 8:09:06 AM Eastern Daylight Time,
mseger@... writes:

<< If you're in the mood to make more
trips like this, I can strongly recommend Williamsburg (including Jamestown,
Yorktown and Carter's Grove), Plymouth Plantation, and Concord and
Lexington. >>

If you are interested in Williamsburg, check their web page
http://www.history.org/

Tickets are regularly $35 for adults. HOWEVER, they hold Home Educators Week
in Jan and Sept where tickets are $8.50 per person. Search for Home Educator
to get more information on the program.

Bush Gardens (a theme park where you can go to England (Shakespeare's time),
France and a few othere European countries) is nearby.

Cynthia
